[{"id":27643,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","q":"<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/b878b509-f206-4070-bf6a-c462160cfc78-image.png\" style=\"width: 483px; height: 90px;\" /></p><p>Consider the above reaction and predict the major product.</p>","question":"<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/b878b509-f206-4070-bf6a-c462160cfc78-image.png\" style=\"width: 483px; height: 90px;\" /></p><p>Consider the above reaction and predict the major product.</p>","options":["<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/1bf873c2-ea5c-4235-af37-d95927109697-image.png\" style=\"width: 346px; height: 70px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/94f580d1-c56f-4df0-9df5-9b7c80e4b7e4-image.png\" style=\"width: 352px; height: 90px;\" /></p>","<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/2dda7458-854d-4202-9b7f-dbbe05b5ec08-image.png\" style=\"width: 361px; height: 90px;\" />","<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/f0b799e6-8b68-4dc0-9bc9-d3eec561a68b-image.png\" style=\"width: 316px; height: 60px;\" /></p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>DiBAL-H is&nbsp;Diisobutylaluminium hydride, which is a very useful reducing agent. It is used for selectively converting ester or nitriles into respective aldehydes. It does not affect other groups like aldehyde or double bond.&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/4ef7aab7-f5fc-4422-8d02-76f9e36b3c9a-dec4377f-1cd8-4a10-ae36-907c1a68790d-image.png\" style=\"width: 396px; height: 231px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null,"_marksId":"648b5a6d417cc3fb48d679d6"},{"id":27688,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","q":"Among the following acids which has the lowest $\\mathrm{pK}_{\\mathrm{a}}$ value","question":"Among the following acids which has the lowest $\\mathrm{pK}_{\\mathrm{a}}$ value","options":["$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COOH}$","$\\mathrm{HCOOH}$","$\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_3\\right)_2 \\mathrm{COOH}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{COOH}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null,"_marksId":"648b5a62417cc3fb48d656aa"},{"id":27625,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","q":"The least acidic compund, among the following is :<br /><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/gYXmx6NeDXn13Tk-EvEVCsed-agjRzZlpslSA9_eGZM.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","question":"The least acidic compund, among the following is :<br /><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/gYXmx6NeDXn13Tk-EvEVCsed-agjRzZlpslSA9_eGZM.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","options":["D","A","B","C"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/O_8Io7VV57ec8Mhu_ZEhR2PDOMMFJIVMD-assmasFTQ.original.fullsize.png\"/><br />C.B. of terminal alkyne will be sp hybridisation and loculised. In other C.B. will be resonance stablised.","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 1)","image":null,"_marksId":"68542ca37c09d044e4c1a307"},{"id":27637,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","q":"<p>The major product &lsquo;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math>&rsquo; formed in the following sequence of reactions is</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/8c153132-f881-459a-9eb2-245195a3a0e8.png\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 134px;\" /></p>","question":"<p>The major product &lsquo;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math>&rsquo; formed in the following sequence of reactions is</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/8c153132-f881-459a-9eb2-245195a3a0e8.png\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 134px;\" /></p>","options":["<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/825774a3-db3d-45a2-bdb3-1becacb9bd9b.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 94px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/59870980-f498-4bd3-8da1-9138418bff01.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 86px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/90d39f45-43b2-4fe8-aee3-78d4e6e75e56.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 97px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/d1a666b5-51ee-4ea3-973d-908ae709c475.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 79px;\" /></p>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>SOCl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;is a halogenating agent. The carboxylic acid group of reactant changes to acid chloride. The acid chloride formed reacts with primary amine to give secondary amide. The secondary amide undergo reduction with lithium aluminium hydride to give secondary amine.</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/5546dec6-cec8-48ad-a320-e802a2d65c26.png\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 196px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null,"_marksId":"648b5a71417cc3fb48d68626"},{"id":27668,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Carboxylic Acid Derivatives","q":"The major product of the following reaction is:<br /><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/1e4bbbe0-ea29-4b60-8867-f2b9a3bb4d1c-image.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 96px;\" />","question":"The major product of the following reaction is:<br /><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/1e4bbbe0-ea29-4b60-8867-f2b9a3bb4d1c-image.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 96px;\" />","options":["<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/c86c2604-2ed7-42fa-95c6-5555ed885721-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 87px;\" />","<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/5f55fc5b-8b17-48b5-a19b-0a957eb535d2-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 94px;\" />","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/c68ca53f-1183-428c-880b-9b3f793be83b-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 138px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/ed90ecfb-136c-4380-a3b1-ba3e80ca5e16-image.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 74px;\" /><br />as <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math> is a better nucleophile than <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null,"_marksId":"648b5a66417cc3fb48d66609"}]